14/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The partners in Macedonia's ruling coalition -- the Social Democratic Alliance for Macedonia, the Liberal Democratic Party and the Democratic Union for Integration -- were expected to continue talks on power decentralisation and the new territorial division package Monday (14 June). 
Power decentralisation is the last step in implementing the Ohrid Peace Accord.
Meanwhile, Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva left Monday for Croatia. 
Her visit will focus on Adriatic Charter co-operation and on ways to implement Charter goals over the next six months. 
(Makfax, A1 TV - 14/06/04)
